.TH sysmaint 1 "" "sysmaint" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
sysmaint \- automated Linux system maintenance
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sysmaint
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sysmaint
is a multi-distro maintenance tool for Linux systems.
It performs package updates, cleanup, security audits,
and emits JSON telemetry.

Supports: Debian/Ubuntu (APT), Red Hat/Fedora (DNF),
Arch (Pacman), SUSE (Zypper), plus Snap and Flatpak.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --dry-run
Preview actions without changes.
.TP
.B --gui, --tui
Interactive menu mode.
.TP
.B --json-summary
Write JSON report to /tmp/system-maintenance/.
.TP
.B --upgrade
Full distribution upgrade.
.TP
.B --purge-kernels
Remove old kernels (use --keep-kernels=N).
.TP
.B --security-audit
Check critical file permissions.
.TP
.B --auto
Unattended mode (no prompts).
.TP
.B --detect
Show system detection report.

Full options: sysmaint --help

.SH FILES
.TP
.B /tmp/system-maintenance/
Logs and JSON output.

.SH EXIT STATUS
0 success; 10 repo issues; 20 missing keys;
30 failed services; 75 lock timeout; 100 reboot required.

